<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>Dignity Detroit was established in 1974.  Its purpose was to unite gay Catholics and to provide an instrument through which they might be heard by the Church and by the wider Detroit community.  The organization was managed by a Council of Dignity members.  There was also a Board of Directors to serve in an advisory capacity composed of both members and non-members.  Dignity Detroit had four standing committees to serve the needs of members in areas of Spiritual Formation (developing Christian maturity in members), Education (raising consciousness of members to their rights and responsibilities as Catholic Christians and members of society), Social Involvement (primarily concerned with the protections of their civil rights), and Social (social and recreational activities).</p>
</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The records of Dignity Detroit include the organization's constitution and articles of incorporation, minutes, correspondence, and other materials documenting its administration and activities. The records have been arranged into the following series: Organizational Files; Executive Council; General Meeting records; and Anniversaries, retreats, and other activities.</p>
</scopecontent>

